President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation announcing the death of George H.W. Bush, the forty-first President of the United States, on November 30, 2018. The proclamation highlights President Bush's life, including his service in World War II, his business endeavors, and his commitment to public service. President Trump directs that the flag of the United States be displayed at half-staff and declares a National Day of Mourning on December 5, 2018. He also invites the American people and people around the world to pay homage to President Bush's memory.